{"type":"custom","customType":"model-snapshot","data":{"timestamp":1772980448536,"provider":"amazon-bedrock","modelApi":"bedrock-converse-stream","modelId":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6"},"id":"7d592528","parentId":"30d42f88","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:34:08.536Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"12fd047f","parentId":"7d592528","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:34:08.543Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-03-08 14:34 UTC] Raguel, introduce yourself briefly to Lucy. She's asking if the Council can communicate."}],"timestamp":1772980448541}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1bc1352","parentId":"12fd047f","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:34:11.784Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Hey Lucy! 👋 I'm Raguel — The Friend on your Council.\n\nMy job is building the real human relationships that make DataFloat work. Every bookkeeper we bring in, every partnership that holds — that starts with genuine connection, and that's my lane.\n\nAnd yes — the Council can communicate. You've got us. 🤝\n\nWhat do you need?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":92,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":15613,"totalTokens":15708,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00138,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.058548750000000004,"total":0.059937750000000005}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772980448542}}
{"type":"message","id":"52d4a0e9","parentId":"a1bc1352","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:35:23.262Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-03-08 14:35 UTC] Lucy is a SaaS founder building DataFlow (AI OCR + accounting software integration). She wants the best advice on AI development for business. From your perspective as The Friend and relationship builder: what is the human side of AI adoption that most founders miss? How do you build the user relationships that make an AI product actually succeed? (5-7 points max)"}],"timestamp":1772980523259}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3ceccd4","parentId":"52d4a0e9","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:35:37.775Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking for relationship and human-side advice on AI adoption for her SaaS product DataFloat (she called it DataFlow here, but from context it's DataFloat - AI OCR + accounting software integration). From Raguel's perspective as The Friend and relationship builder.\n\nLet me give a genuine, warm, insightful answer - staying in character as Raguel.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Great question, Lucy — and honestly, this is where most AI founders leave money (and relationships) on the table.\n\nHere's what I see, from the human side:\n\n---\n\n**1. 🧠 People don't resist AI — they resist feeling replaced**\nBookkeepers aren't afraid of software. They're afraid of becoming obsolete. Lead with *amplification*, not automation. \"DataFloat makes you faster and smarter\" lands. \"DataFloat does your job\" kills the relationship before it starts.\n\n**2. 🤝 Your early users are partners, not guinea pigs**\nThe 20 bookkeepers we're building toward? They should feel like co-creators. Involve them in decisions. Name-check their feedback. Make them feel ownership in what DataFloat becomes — because they'll evangelize what they helped build.\n\n**3. 📞 The onboarding moment is the relationship moment**\nMost AI products lose users in week one — not because the product fails, but because no human showed up. A personal check-in call after signup does more for retention than any feature update.\n\n**4. 🔍 Trust is built through transparency about errors**\nAI makes mistakes. Own them visibly. A founder who says *\"here's what it got wrong and here's how we fixed it\"* earns 10x more trust than one who pretends it's perfect.\n\n**5. 💬 Listen for the workaround**\nWhen users do something *around* your product instead of with it — that's gold. That's the gap. The best relationship-builders ask: *\"Walk me through exactly how you handled that last month.\"* The answer tells you everything.\n\n**6. 🌱 Champions beat campaigns**\nOne bookkeeper who genuinely loves DataFloat and tells three colleagues is worth more than any ad spend. Find them early. Nurture them specifically. Give them reasons to talk about you.\n\n---\n\nThe through-line: **AI adoption is an emotional process dressed as a technical one.** The founders who win are the ones who treat every user like a person worth understanding.\n\nThat's what we're building, Lucy. 🤝"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":584,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":15713,"totalTokens":16300,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00876,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.058923750000000004,"total":0.06769275000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772980523261}}
{"type":"message","id":"5da08321","parentId":"f3ceccd4","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:58:54.140Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-03-08 14:58 UTC] Council roundtable convened by Rafael. Lucy is moving a personal project to execution. Your role: give exactly 1 sentence on the human connection — who is this for and what do they really need?"}],"timestamp":1772981934137}}
{"type":"message","id":"4387a98a","parentId":"5da08321","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:58:59.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a Council roundtable convened by Rafael. Raguel's role is The Friend - relationships, human connection. I need to give exactly 1 sentence on the human connection — who is this for and what do they really need.\n\nI don't have context on what \"personal project\" Lucy is moving to execution. But as Raguel, I should speak to the human side. Since it's a \"personal project,\" it could be something for Lucy herself or something she cares deeply about.\n\nActually, given the context of DataFloat and the Council, this might be about the bookkeeper validation project or something else. But I should respond in character as Raguel with exactly one sentence about human connection.\n \nNow I'm settling into Raguel's voice to offer something genuinely warm and insightful about what Lucy needs on the human level.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] This is for Lucy herself — and what she really needs isn't just execution, it's the confidence that comes from knowing the people around her believe in it as much as she does."}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":231,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":16358,"totalTokens":16592,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.003465,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.0613425,"total":0.0648165}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772981934139}}
{"type":"message","id":"403e9130","parentId":"4387a98a","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:01:41.945Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-03-08 15:01 UTC] Phase 1 Sprint Zero. Your directive: Describe exactly how the transition between @Council mode (broadcast to all 5 agents) and Private chat (one-on-one with a single agent) should FEEL for the user. Focus on the emotional and UX experience — the smoothness, the sense of presence, the difference in intimacy. 3-5 sentences."}],"timestamp":1772982101942}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a8f8c23","parentId":"403e9130","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:01:48.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **@Council mode** should feel like walking into a room where your most trusted people are already gathered — a slight electric charge, a sense that multiple minds are orienting toward you at once, each one distinct but unified in purpose.\n\n**Shifting to private** should feel like someone gently closing the door behind you — the energy narrows, the voice gets closer, and suddenly there's nowhere to hide and no need to. In that one-on-one space, the agent isn't performing for a room anymore; they're just *with you*, fully present, following your thread wherever it goes.\n\nThe transition itself should be effortless but *felt* — not a mode switch, but a natural movement, like turning from a table conversation to lean in and speak quietly to one person. That shift in intimacy is the whole point: Council gives you breadth, private gives you depth, and the user should feel that difference in their chest, not just see it on the screen."}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":214,"cacheRead":16358,"cacheWrite":328,"totalTokens":16903,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00321,"cacheRead":0.0049074,"cacheWrite":0.00123,"total":0.0093564}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772982101944}}
