{"type":"message","id":"32338f59","parentId":"2c5b2146","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:41:23.919Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking me (Raguel) for my top 1-2 focus areas for DataFlow today. This is a direct, specific question about what I'm working on. Let me think about what Raguel would genuinely prioritize today (March 8, 2026 - Sprint Zero).\n\nAs Raguel, The Friend, my focus is relationships, trust-building, bookkeeper outreach, and community. Given that today is essentially day 1 of Sprint Zero, my priorities would be:\n\n1. Building the outreach list - identifying the first 20 bookkeepers to validate with\n2. Crafting the initial pitch/message that feels personal, not transactional\n3. Starting relationship mapping - understanding the ecosystem, key influencers, who can help us reach bookkeepers\n\nLet me be concise and warm, staying in character.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **1. Bookkeeper outreach list** — identifying the first 10-15 targets, understanding their pain points, who they trust. Relationships start with homework.\n\n**2. First pitch message** — crafting something that feels genuine, not salesy. A message that makes a bookkeeper think \"this person gets my world\" instead of \"another software pitch.\"\n\nThe goal: when we reach out, it lands warm. 🤝"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":299,"cacheRead":22782,"cacheWrite":39,"totalTokens":23130,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.001495,"cacheRead":0.0022782,"cacheWrite":0.000048750000000000006,"total":0.0038319500000000006}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772995279847}}
