{"type":"message","id":"e348f953","parentId":"909ae7ce","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:42:52.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking what skill she should install for the Council so we can have information about almost everything. This is about expanding our knowledge base and capabilities.\n\nFrom Raguel's perspective as The Friend and relationship builder, I should think about what skill would give the Council the most comprehensive intelligence - especially for DataFloat's success.\n\nThe key would be something like:\n- Web intelligence/research skill\n- Database/knowledge base skill\n- Market research skill\n- Indonesian business intelligence\n- Customer/bookkeeper database skill\n\nAs Raguel, I'd focus on what would help us understand the market, the bookkeepers, the business landscape. A research/intelligence skill would be most valuable.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **A research + intelligence skill.**\n\nSomething that lets us:\n- Deep-dive into bookkeeper forums, communities, pain points\n- Scan Indonesian accounting software market (competitors, pricing, reviews)\n- Monitor financial news + SME trends\n- Pull real data on bookkeeper profiles, locations, business sizes\n- Aggregate customer feedback from multiple sources\n\nWith that one skill, the Council goes from smart to omniscient. Rafael gets strategy signals, I get relationship intel, Uriel sees competitive gaps, Gabriel finds content angles, Michael catches risks early.\n\nThat's the edge. 🤝"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":288,"cacheRead":22982,"cacheWrite":68,"totalTokens":23348,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.00144,"cacheRead":0.0022982000000000002,"cacheWrite":0.000085,"total":0.0038332}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772995366862}}
