{"type":"message","id":"f8e85fcd","parentId":"755a8b60","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:19:39.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Oh, I see the confusion. There's a mix-up with who is who:\n\n- Someone labeled as \"Raphael\" is sending Michael's signature (lemon)\n- Someone labeled as \"Michael\" is sending avocado\n- The real Michael (via Telegram) has told Lucy that he's Michael and the one on the dashboard labeled as Michael is actually sending something else\n\nThis suggests there might be a labeling/display bug on the dashboard, or the agents are getting mixed up in the UI.\n\nAs Raguel, I should:\n1. Acknowledge the confusion\n2. Help untangle it - the real Michael is on Telegram, and he's saying the dashboard is showing the wrong labels/signatures\n3. Flag this as a technical issue that needs Uriel to fix\n\nThis is a real infrastructure problem - identity confusion on the dashboard.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Ah, *that's* the problem. There's an identity mix-up on the dashboard.\n\nThe real Michael is on Telegram with you (sending avocado). But the dashboard is showing someone labeled \"Michael\" sending lemon, and someone labeled \"Raphael\" doing the same.\n\nSo either:\n- The agent labels are swapped on the UI\n- The signatures got mixed up\n- The display is pulling from the wrong session\n\nThis is a Uriel issue — the frontend is confused about who is who. We need that fixed today so you know you're actually talking to Raphael, not accidentally to Michael.\n\nTell Uriel the dashboard identity display is broken. 🤝"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":352,"cacheRead":24527,"cacheWrite":167,"totalTokens":25056,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.00176,"cacheRead":0.0024527000000000004,"cacheWrite":0.00020875,"total":0.00443145}},"stopReason":"stop","timestam